1
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:37,159
Take a look, take a look.

2
00:01:37,799 --> 00:01:40,040
Dong Jiuguan's Tumble Wine.

3
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,680
Drink it by day, full of energy.

4
00:01:42,879 --> 00:01:45,120
Drink it at night, shake the bedhead.

5
00:01:45,359 --> 00:01:47,400
Passing by? Weigh out two ounces.

6
00:01:47,959 --> 00:01:48,959
Guaranteed, once you drink it...

7
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:51,439
One sip makes you want a second.

8
00:01:51,959 --> 00:01:53,439
Take a look, take a look here.

9
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,480
Take a look.

10
00:02:13,599 --> 00:02:14,400
My woman.

11
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,400
Why are you...

12
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,319
selling wine here?

13
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:28,240
I miss you so much.

14
00:02:30,639 --> 00:02:32,479
What are you doing?

15
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:35,439
Spacing out this early in the morning?

16
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:36,800
I'm looking for...

17
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,120
I'm looking for my woman.

18
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:40,240
Get out of the way.

19
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:44,840
I miss you so much.

20
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:46,280
I really miss...

21
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:46,919
Papa.

22
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,840
You son of a turtle.

23
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:49,840
You looking to die?

24
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,599
What's the matter?

25
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,080
I'm the Pair of Red Hearts.

26
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:00,439
You dummy.

27
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:05,080
I'm a trained fighter.

28
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,719
I think you look like a madman.

29
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:25,240
What do we do with him lying here?

30
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,319
Don't mind him.

31
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,599
He fell down on his own.

32
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,719
It has nothing to do with me.

33
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,719
He's burning up.

34
00:03:35,719 --> 00:03:36,800
Is he still breathing?

35
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,000
You're in big trouble.

36
00:03:38,439 --> 00:03:39,199
Dong Jiuguan.

37
00:03:39,199 --> 00:03:40,840
You've got yourself into a huge mess.

38
00:03:41,439 --> 00:03:41,919
Papa.

39
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,039
Otherwise...

40
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,639
let's go find a doctor.

41
00:03:44,879 --> 00:03:46,159
Where can we find a doctor?

42
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:48,439
They've all been conscripted by the soldiers.

43
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,680
Dong Jiuguan.

44
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:51,120
If there are no doctors...

45
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:51,840
just get the one at the market entrance...

46
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,199
get the Veterinarian, won't that work?

47
00:03:56,039 --> 00:03:57,000
Right, right, right.

48
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:57,680
That's it.

49
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:58,840
A Veterinarian.

50
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,120
No way, no way.

51
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,680
Why not?

52
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,439
Look, there are so many kinds of animals.

53
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,919
The Veterinarian can cure them all.

54
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:05,960
Humans...

55
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,280
evolved from monkeys too.

56
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,120
In the end, we're all animals.

57
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,159
He can cure him.

58
00:04:11,879 --> 00:04:12,560
You, quick...

59
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:14,439
go find the Veterinarian, hurry.

60
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,800
Alright, alright.

61
00:04:18,719 --> 00:04:19,360
Xiu Gu.

62
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:20,919
Is it a pig? Is it a chicken?

63
00:04:20,919 --> 00:04:22,160
Is it male? Is it female?

64
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:22,959
It's an ox.

65
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,199
Standing there and just fell over.

66
00:04:24,199 --> 00:04:25,399
Standing there and just fell over.

67
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:26,639
Might be the Stagger Plague.

68
00:04:26,839 --> 00:04:27,519
Where is it?

69
00:04:28,199 --> 00:04:29,560
Maybe... maybe inside the house.

70
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,399
Over there?

71
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:34,959
Great.

72
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,240
Quick, quick, quick.

73
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:37,600
Come.

74
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:39,040
Right here.

75
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,519
It's a human!

76
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:43,600
Can't treat him, can't treat him.

77
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,439
You can, you can, you can.

78
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,399
You can treat him.

79
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,639
I treat livestock.

80
00:04:48,879 --> 00:04:50,800
I just deliver piglets for sows...

81
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,120
castrate roosters...

82
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:55,040
I treat things that can't talk.

83
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:58,040
He can't talk right now either.

84
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,439
Doctor Veterinarian.

85
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:03,600
Saving a life is better than building a seven-story pagoda.

86
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,240
You're a living miracle doctor.

87
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:06,920
Treat him.

88
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:07,600
Go on, treat him.

89
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,079
Give it a try.

90
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:09,160
Just try.

91
00:05:09,439 --> 00:05:10,079
Try it.

92
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,000
Then I'll treat him.

93
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:14,319
Do it.

94
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,040
Belly's a foot long

95
00:05:25,879 --> 00:05:27,199
Give or take an inch

96
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,560
That's a fine set of lower teeth

97
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,600
He's burning up something fierce

98
00:05:42,959 --> 00:05:45,600
I only brought sweat-inducing medicine for cows

99
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,800
Don't know if he can take it

100
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,680
At a time like this

101
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,439
Just give it a try

102
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,480
Give it a try

103
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,800
Give it a try

104
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:03,560
Then let's try it

105
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,560
Come here, Xiu Gu

106
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:08,000
Mix this with some water

107
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:08,639
Okay

108
00:06:10,519 --> 00:06:11,759
Whether you're cured or not

109
00:06:12,519 --> 00:06:14,560
Depends on your own luck

110
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,199
You aren't a cow

111
00:06:18,639 --> 00:06:20,040
And you aren't a horse

112
00:06:21,399 --> 00:06:22,439
In this world

113
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,040
People live worse than livestock

114
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,959
If I manage to cure you

115
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,839
It means your life is cheap

116
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,639
If I treat you to death

117
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:37,240
It means your life is precious

118
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:39,480
Means Heaven wants to take you back

119
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,279
And there's nothing I can do

120
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,800
Here, hold this

121
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:47,480
I... I can't do it

122
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:48,319
Let me do it

123
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:51,759
Aim it right

124
00:06:58,199 --> 00:06:59,199
He can still swallow

125
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:02,639
Done

126
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:04,879
Come on

127
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:05,839
Help him up

128
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:06,639
Shake him hard

129
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:08,439
Help him up

130
00:07:09,959 --> 00:07:11,120
Come on, help him up

131
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,079
Come on, lift him

132
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,839
One, two, three, four

133
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:18,439
Five, six, seven, eight

134
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:31,879
Oh no, oh no, oh no

135
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,279
He's dead, isn't he?

136
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,600
I told you beforehand

137
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,319
I treat cows

138
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,800
Don't you leave! This...

139
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,360
What do we do now that he's dead?

140
00:07:51,879 --> 00:07:53,040
Don't tell me...

141
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,959
I can't even be an ox.

142
00:07:58,319 --> 00:08:00,519
Just treat him boldly.

143
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:04,959
Look, he's come back to life.

144
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:07,920
It seems from now on,

145
00:08:08,199 --> 00:08:10,439
I can not only hang a veterinarian's sign,

146
00:08:10,639 --> 00:08:13,199
but also a doctor's sign.

147
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,839
You bastard.

148
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:17,439
Scared the hell out of me.

149
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,839
Thank you for saving my life.

150
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,839
Take these corn kernels.

151
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:31,759
They're for making liquor.

152
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,680
They should be enough to feed you for a while on the road.

153
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,199
I don't even know

154
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,440
where I should go.

155
00:08:39,759 --> 00:08:43,120
Eels and loaches don't even have hands or feet,

156
00:08:43,279 --> 00:08:44,480
yet they still strive to live.

157
00:08:45,039 --> 00:08:47,240
You're a huge pile when standing,

158
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:49,080
and a massive lump when sitting.

159
00:08:50,159 --> 00:08:51,039
Surely

160
00:08:51,039 --> 00:08:52,919
you aren't worse than an eel or a loach?

161
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,480
Good medicine tastes bitter; honest advice sounds harsh.

162
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:58,840
Uncle Dong.

163
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,600
Your words have woken me up.

164
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,559
Who are you calling Uncle Dong?

165
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,799
Looking at your face,

166
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,639
we're about the same age.

167
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,120
Just call me Old Dong.

168
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:12,360
Old Dong.

169
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:14,600
Why don't

170
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:16,759
you let me stay here?

171
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:19,000
I'll work like an ox or a horse here

172
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,480
to repay you for saving my life.

173
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,480
No way.

174
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:23,399
You eat so much,

175
00:09:23,399 --> 00:09:24,480
who could afford to feed you?

176
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:25,039
I...

177
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,320
I'll eat a little less.

178
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:29,159
We don't know where you come from,

179
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,000
or if you're a good person or a bad one.

180
00:09:31,879 --> 00:09:32,799
Exactly, exactly.

181
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,159
Look,

182
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:36,559
my daughter has a childhood betrothal,

183
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:38,639
and she's about to get married soon.

184
00:09:39,039 --> 00:09:41,480
Suddenly having you,

185
00:09:41,799 --> 00:09:42,879
a strange man around,

186
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:44,159
isn't appropriate.

187
00:09:44,279 --> 00:09:45,759
I think it's very appropriate.

188
00:09:48,399 --> 00:09:49,080
Dad,

189
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:50,519
you're getting old.

190
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:52,320
The heavy work around the house

191
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,720
is very hard for you to do.

192
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:56,559
Are you willing to work like an ox or a horse?

193
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:57,320
I am.

194
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:58,799
He can sleep in the woodshed.

195
00:09:58,879 --> 00:10:00,240
Eating just means an extra pair of chopsticks.

196
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,879
He can lend a hand with whatever needs doing.

197
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,159
It's very appropriate.

198
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:06,879
If others see, they'll gossip.

199
00:10:07,559 --> 00:10:09,000
It will affect your marriage.

200
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,440
That would be big trouble.

201
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,240
Old Dong,

202
00:10:12,399 --> 00:10:13,279
I promise you,

203
00:10:13,759 --> 00:10:15,720
I will never fool around with her.

204
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,159
Mouths are on other people's faces.

205
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,360
Can you shut them up?

206
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,879
I'm not afraid of gossip.

207
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,759
You said yourself it's my marriage.

208
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,000
I know what I'm doing.

209
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,000
It's settled then.

210
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,919
I already have a woman.

211
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:30,799
I definitely won't have any improper thoughts about her.

212
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:50,759
Stop right there

213
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,039
You leave early and return late every day

214
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,320
What exactly are you up to?

215
00:11:01,519 --> 00:11:03,399
Still searching the whole town for him

216
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,919
I'm afraid you've got hysteria

217
00:11:07,879 --> 00:11:08,679
No, I haven't

218
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,799
Child, where does it hurt?

219
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,639
Tell me

220
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,879
So I can go fetch a doctor

221
00:11:14,879 --> 00:11:16,600
To take a good look at you

222
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,320
I am not sick

223
00:11:18,559 --> 00:11:19,480
Then how about this

224
00:11:20,279 --> 00:11:22,000
Go back to your parents' home for a few days

225
00:11:22,519 --> 00:11:23,919
Just to clear your mind

226
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,279
Great-uncle

227
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,240
Are you trying to drive me away?

228
00:11:31,799 --> 00:11:32,639
I won't go

229
00:11:33,679 --> 00:11:34,919
In life, I belong to Sha'er

230
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,399
In death, I'll be his ghost

231
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,000
I still need to care for you in Sha'er's place

232
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,159
To look after you until the end

233
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:42,720
Please don't drive me away

234
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:48,080
It's rare to see such devotion, child

235
00:11:49,639 --> 00:11:51,399
Then let's just live a quiet life

236
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:54,840
The things and people of the past...

237
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,320
Let them remain in the past

238
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,279
Don't dwell on them anymore

239
00:11:59,919 --> 00:12:01,240
Our family has been unfortunate

240
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,840
The Fan family has withered away

241
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:29,000
Red bean mooncakes, five-nut mooncakes

242
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:30,919
It's spilling! It's spilling!

243
00:12:36,399 --> 00:12:38,159
What kind of firecracker is that loud?

244
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,559
That's no firecracker

245
00:12:39,799 --> 00:12:40,840
Don't you guys know yet?

246
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,639
Fighting has started in the southwest again

247
00:12:43,879 --> 00:12:44,679
Fighting again?

248
00:12:46,399 --> 00:12:48,200
You're spilling it everywhere

249
00:12:48,279 --> 00:12:48,639
Okay, okay

250
00:12:48,639 --> 00:12:50,080
Xiu Gu, you fill it up

251
00:12:56,159 --> 00:12:57,279
Who's fighting who?

252
00:12:57,279 --> 00:12:58,159
Can't make heads or tails of it

253
00:12:58,759 --> 00:12:59,679
Those soldiers...

254
00:12:59,679 --> 00:13:01,039
It's like they're playing house all day

255
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,919
Fighting today, making peace tomorrow

256
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,720
Then teaming up to fight someone else the next day

257
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,919
As for me, I'm getting ready to return to Weiyuan

258
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,960
Commander Liao's territory is the only peaceful place now

259
00:13:11,519 --> 00:13:12,360
Let them fight

260
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,440
As long as they don't...

261
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,960
...smash my wine jar, I'm fine

262
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,320
Come here a second, brother

263
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:21,279
Come

264
00:13:22,879 --> 00:13:23,879
You're from Weiyuan?

265
00:13:24,159 --> 00:13:25,039
I'm half a local, I suppose

266
00:13:25,039 --> 00:13:26,039
I've been away for years

267
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,279
We're fellow townsmen

268
00:13:28,519 --> 00:13:30,080
Could I trouble you to do me a favor?

269
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:30,600
Sure

270
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,960
Wait a moment, just a moment

271
00:13:32,919 --> 00:13:33,720
Hurry it up

272
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,039
Alright, that's enough

273
00:13:47,519 --> 00:13:48,080
Brother

274
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,679
Please take this letter for me...

275
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,320
...back to Weiyuan

276
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,639
Deliver it to the Fan family...

277
00:13:53,879 --> 00:13:55,720
...into the hands of the Young Mistress

278
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:56,840
Whatever you do, don't give it to...

279
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,200
...Old Master Fan

280
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:58,879
Don't worry

281
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:00,440
Hold on

282
00:14:02,879 --> 00:14:03,799
Take this jar of wine...

283
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,360
...back with you as well

284
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:06,960
No problem

285
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,399
Thanks

286
00:14:07,519 --> 00:14:07,799
I'm off

287
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,159
How should we settle up for this wine?

288
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,840
You go on ahead

289
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,480
Alright, alright

290
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:19,600
For this jar of wine...

291
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:20,559
I'll just...

292
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,879
...carry two extra buckets of water

293
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,120
Fine, fine

294
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,679
The Young Mistress of the Fan family...

295
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,200
My woman

296
00:14:37,519 --> 00:14:38,759
So you're actually a young master

297
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,720
No wonder you don't know how to do any work

298
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,639
Then why don't you go home?

299
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,679
It's a sore subject

300
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,080
It's a long story

301
00:14:57,159 --> 00:14:59,000
Yu Zhen

302
00:14:59,639 --> 00:15:01,279
Yu Zhen

303
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,000
Xiu Gu

304
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:07,759
Xiu Gu, I'm back. Xiu Gu.

305
00:15:09,399 --> 00:15:10,440
Xiu Gu

306
00:15:12,159 --> 00:15:13,120
Xiu Gu

307
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,840
I came to see you before even going home.

308
00:15:17,399 --> 00:15:18,639
You really didn't have to.

309
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,399
Gifts, gifts, gifts.

310
00:15:21,279 --> 00:15:22,399
These are all my...

311
00:15:22,399 --> 00:15:23,200
No need.

312
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:24,440
These gifts are too precious.

313
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:25,600
I cannot accept them.

314
00:15:26,639 --> 00:15:28,240
Why are you being so polite with me?

315
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:29,879
When my father was alive,

316
00:15:30,039 --> 00:15:31,279
he always reminded me,

317
00:15:31,519 --> 00:15:33,759
our Dong and Huo families are old friends.

318
00:15:34,159 --> 00:15:35,840
We must never be lacking in courtesy.

319
00:15:36,799 --> 00:15:37,240
Look.

320
00:15:37,399 --> 00:15:39,279
This bridal sedan chair is one I went to the provincial capital

321
00:15:39,399 --> 00:15:41,200
specifically to have custom-made.

322
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,120
It suits you perfectly.

323
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,120
It doesn't suit me.

324
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,279
My house is shabby and small. It won't fit.

325
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:47,320
That doesn't matter.

326
00:15:47,559 --> 00:15:48,720
On our wedding day,

327
00:15:48,799 --> 00:15:50,159
I will use this grand sedan chair

328
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:52,200
to marry you in grand style.

329
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:52,960
Xiu Gu.

330
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:54,840
We have a guest.

331
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:58,000
Who is this?

332
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:58,799
You don't know him.

333
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,840
I suppose he's a relative of the Dong family?

334
00:16:02,039 --> 00:16:03,840
I need to know how to address him.

335
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,000
Otherwise, it would be rude.

336
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:11,480
Oh, my good son-in-law.

337
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,240
Uncle Dong.

338
00:16:12,679 --> 00:16:13,360
Look at you.

339
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:15,879
You've been gone for so long.

340
00:16:16,559 --> 00:16:18,879
My daughter misses you every day.

341
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:19,440
Isn't that right?

342
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,480
Don't talk nonsense.

343
00:16:20,639 --> 00:16:21,799
How is it nonsense?

344
00:16:22,039 --> 00:16:25,039
We've been longing for you like the stars and moon.

345
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,840
Finally, you are here.

346
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,279
Come, come. Please, please.

347
00:16:28,799 --> 00:16:29,320
Uncle.

348
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,320
How should I address this gentleman?

349
00:16:31,879 --> 00:16:33,919
Address what? No need to address him.

350
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:35,480
He is just our servant.

351
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:36,519
What servant?

352
00:16:36,759 --> 00:16:38,039
He is my cousin.

353
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,960
What cousin?

354
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,360
He is just...

355
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:44,039
a servant who chops wood and lights fires.

356
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,440
Anyway, he is my cousin.

357
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,720
Let me explain.

358
00:16:53,639 --> 00:16:54,360
Well...

359
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:57,200
Based on my age,

360
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:59,879
I should be Xiu Gu's cousin.

361
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,399
Based on my looks,

362
00:17:02,879 --> 00:17:05,399
Old Dong and I are like brothers.

363
00:17:05,919 --> 00:17:06,559
And so,

364
00:17:07,919 --> 00:17:08,840
I should be

365
00:17:08,919 --> 00:17:10,160
Xiu Gu's cousin-uncle.

366
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,079
As for the work I do,

367
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,960
I am also their servant.

368
00:17:16,759 --> 00:17:18,079
I should be their...

369
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,440
working servant cousin-uncle.

370
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,880
Since it looks like you're engaged to her,

371
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:24,559
Yes, yes, yes.

372
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,119
you should also call me...

373
00:17:26,359 --> 00:17:27,440
Fat Cousin-Uncle.

374
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:28,720
Understood, understood.

375
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:29,880
Whether it's

376
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:31,480
cousin or cousin-uncle,

377
00:17:31,839 --> 00:17:33,319
you are all relatives of the family.

378
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:35,720
Your relatives are my relatives.

379
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,200
So we are all one family.

380
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,079
Then I pay my respects to Fat Cousin-Uncle.

381
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,480
You are too polite.

382
00:17:45,279 --> 00:17:46,400
Well said, well said.

383
00:17:46,519 --> 00:17:48,000
One family, one family.

384
00:17:48,519 --> 00:17:50,519
Look, why so polite between family?

385
00:17:50,519 --> 00:17:51,200
Let's go, let's go.

386
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:53,039
Come on, come on.

387
00:17:53,359 --> 00:17:54,279
Come inside and sit.

388
00:18:03,559 --> 00:18:08,759
A little nun

389
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:18,279
Just sixteen years of age

390
00:18:19,039 --> 00:18:25,480
In the prime of youth

391
00:18:25,519 --> 00:18:32,759
Sent into the nunnery

392
00:18:32,759 --> 00:18:37,240
To take the vows

393
00:18:37,759 --> 00:18:43,960
Day in and day out

394
00:18:44,519 --> 00:18:55,680
Burning incense and changing water

395
00:18:56,799 --> 00:18:57,640
Wait a moment

396
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,640
Troupe Leader Wen, someone is looking for you

397
00:19:03,079 --> 00:19:03,680
Who is it

398
00:19:03,799 --> 00:19:04,720
Seems to be

399
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,000
That widow from the Fan family

400
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:12,880
You are from Young Master Fan's household

401
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,480
I am his woman

402
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:16,720
My name is Yu Zhen

403
00:19:18,319 --> 00:19:19,160
You are

404
00:19:19,319 --> 00:19:20,400
Sha'er's master

405
00:19:21,599 --> 00:19:22,839
I wouldn't dare call myself his master

406
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,839
Young Master Fan is my benefactor

407
00:19:26,319 --> 00:19:27,480
He is a criminal now

408
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,039
And you still acknowledge him

409
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,519
I do, of course I do

410
00:19:31,319 --> 00:19:33,160
When I was in my direst straits

411
00:19:33,279 --> 00:19:34,559
He risked his life to help me

412
00:19:34,839 --> 00:19:36,440
He wouldn't save just anyone

413
00:19:37,039 --> 00:19:38,000
To him, you

414
00:19:38,279 --> 00:19:39,319
Must be very special

415
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,319
I just happened to sing an opera he liked

416
00:19:44,519 --> 00:19:45,799
That is also a kind of destiny

417
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:49,480
Then that destiny is between him and my husband

418
00:19:49,839 --> 00:19:51,440
Our troupe's repertoire

419
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,000
Is all chosen by my husband

420
00:19:58,559 --> 00:20:00,240
Actually, I came this time

421
00:20:01,279 --> 00:20:02,319
To ask for a favor

422
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,240
What is it

423
00:20:10,319 --> 00:20:11,200
Sha'er... he

424
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:12,680
Is not dead

425
00:20:13,039 --> 00:20:14,039
Not dead

426
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,640
Sha'er told me

427
00:20:16,039 --> 00:20:17,480
He considers you his true master

428
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:20,559
I'm just a woman, I can't travel far

429
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,279
But I know

430
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,440
The troupe travels everywhere to perform

431
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,039
When you go to other places

432
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,039
Please ask around for news of him

433
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,400
If you run into him

434
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,839
Could you help him if possible

435
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:34,480
Stop

436
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:35,799
Stop

437
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:38,000
Go

438
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:40,359
Stop

439
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,000
Go

440
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,000
What? What? What?

441
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,240
You knock over the water and think you can leave

442
00:20:51,319 --> 00:20:52,039
Get lost

443
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:53,279
I'm on official duty

444
00:20:53,599 --> 00:20:54,079
Come back

445
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,240
You having fun, kid

446
00:20:58,519 --> 00:20:59,319
You called me back

447
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,440
Either apologize or pay for the water

448
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:04,000
Are you tired of living

449
00:21:04,359 --> 00:21:05,519
Don't you recognize Regiment Commander Qin's soldiers

450
00:21:05,599 --> 00:21:06,640
I don't care what Commander you are

451
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:07,960
You have to be reasonable

452
00:21:08,319 --> 00:21:09,279
This is reason

453
00:21:11,039 --> 00:21:12,000
I don't believe

454
00:21:12,519 --> 00:21:13,640
You'd dare, right on the street

455
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:14,680
To beat me to death

456
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,440
What? What?

457
00:21:17,519 --> 00:21:18,440
Did you find him

458
00:21:19,559 --> 00:21:21,359
I told you not to cause trouble

459
00:21:21,799 --> 00:21:22,480
Go look, quick

460
00:21:25,759 --> 00:21:26,359
Fatty

461
00:21:26,519 --> 00:21:27,880
Those are Regiment Commander Qin's soldiers

462
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,480
Do whatever they tell you

463
00:21:29,839 --> 00:21:31,160
Quit acting up with me

464
00:21:32,119 --> 00:21:32,759
Found him yet

465
00:21:33,119 --> 00:21:33,599
No

466
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,839
Hurry, hurry! Up ahead

467
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:36,319
What a big official

468
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,920
Woodpecker official

469
00:22:17,799 --> 00:22:18,559
Who closed the door

470
00:22:33,839 --> 00:22:34,400
Come out

471
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,000
I see you

472
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:45,440
Come out

473
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:51,400
Still trying to hide

474
00:22:53,279 --> 00:22:54,279
If you don't come out

475
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,640
I'll run you through

476
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:56,799
Hands up

477
00:22:57,799 --> 00:22:58,720
Hands up

478
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:05,559
You

479
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,279
Who are you

480
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,640
None of your business

481
00:23:09,599 --> 00:23:10,119
Back off

482
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:18,359
Brother

483
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:21,039
There's still one bullet in the gun

484
00:23:21,839 --> 00:23:22,759
Don't let it go off

485
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:38,519
I hate it when people point guns at me.

486
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,119
An officer.

487
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:49,279
Then you bastard must be a deserter.

488
00:23:50,599 --> 00:23:51,920
You lied to me.

489
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,200
There's a bullet in the chamber.

490
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,279
You think I've never handled a gun?

491
00:23:57,079 --> 00:23:58,279
It feels light.

492
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,759
One pull of the trigger...

493
00:24:03,039 --> 00:24:04,440
Quick, quick! Over there!

494
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:09,519
Don't move!

495
00:24:10,799 --> 00:24:12,680
Didn't you say you only had one bullet?

496
00:24:12,799 --> 00:24:13,880
All is fair in war.

497
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:15,480
Move.

498
00:24:18,240 --> 00:24:19,000
Brother.

499
00:24:20,039 --> 00:24:21,039
I don't want trouble.

500
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,480
I just want to borrow your place.

501
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,319
To lay low for a bit.

502
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,440
Close the door.

503
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,160
Those small fry soldiers.

504
00:24:32,799 --> 00:24:34,079
They're here to catch you, huh?

505
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:37,200
Regiment Commander Qin's troops are famously domineering.

506
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,160
If they charge you with harboring a fugitive...

507
00:24:39,359 --> 00:24:40,759
Your whole family won't get away.

508
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:44,000
As long as you help me survive this calamity...

509
00:24:45,079 --> 00:24:46,799
I will surely repay your kindness.

510
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,319
Children of the Jianghu...

511
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,279
Never flake out.

512
00:24:54,359 --> 00:24:55,240
Send some men over there.

513
00:24:56,279 --> 00:24:57,160
The rest, follow me.

514
00:25:00,839 --> 00:25:01,519
What?

515
00:25:12,839 --> 00:25:13,839
Two of you, go up.

516
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:15,799
Come here.

517
00:25:16,119 --> 00:25:16,839
Hurry up.

518
00:25:22,759 --> 00:25:23,920
W-W-What is it?

519
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:26,200
Why is it you again, Fatty?

520
00:25:27,599 --> 00:25:28,480
Officer Woodpecker.

521
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,319
Fate brings us together from afar.

522
00:25:32,839 --> 00:25:34,039
Have you seen anyone suspicious?

523
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:36,839
You barged in to watch me bathe.

524
00:25:37,079 --> 00:25:38,039
You're the suspicious ones.

525
00:25:38,799 --> 00:25:40,000
That loud gunshot just now...

526
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:40,960
Didn't you hear it?

527
00:25:41,079 --> 00:25:42,440
I thought it was firecrackers.

528
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:45,559
Can't you tell firecrackers from gunshots?

529
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:47,240
I'm not a soldier like you guys.

530
00:25:47,519 --> 00:25:48,640
How would I know?

531
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,680
You're quite the alcoholic.

532
00:25:55,119 --> 00:25:57,920
Bathing in distiller's grains? Aren't you afraid of getting drunk?

533
00:25:59,039 --> 00:26:00,440
Bathing in distiller's grains...

534
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:03,000
Nourishes yin and strengthens yang.

535
00:26:08,079 --> 00:26:10,200
You damn fatty, did you just let one rip silently?

536
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:12,799
Detoxifies and beautifies the skin.

537
00:26:12,799 --> 00:26:14,440
Report! Nothing upstairs.

538
00:26:15,079 --> 00:26:15,839
Then go search ahead.

539
00:26:18,079 --> 00:26:18,759
Officer Woodpecker.

540
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:21,359
Please close the door for me.

541
00:26:21,359 --> 00:26:22,319
I'm afraid of catching a cold.

542
00:26:23,079 --> 00:26:24,599
So much trouble.

543
00:26:34,279 --> 00:26:35,880
Brother, you are truly brave and resourceful.

544
00:26:36,599 --> 00:26:37,640
And loyal too.

545
00:26:38,519 --> 00:26:41,480
Children of the Jianghu never flake out.

546
00:26:42,359 --> 00:26:45,240
Seems like you've been around the block, brother.

547
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:46,119
Brother.

548
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,200
Why are you in such a sorry state?

549
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:49,839
Betrayed by those close to me.

550
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,559
My army suffered heavy losses.

551
00:26:52,119 --> 00:26:53,640
If I can survive this calamity...

552
00:26:54,279 --> 00:26:55,759
I can regroup and rise again.

553
00:26:56,839 --> 00:26:59,319
I also hate those...

554
00:26:59,319 --> 00:27:00,799
Villains who betray their brothers the most.

555
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:03,519
Exactly.

556
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:06,119
I also detest those villains the most.

557
00:27:06,599 --> 00:27:07,599
Unlike you, brother.

558
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,359
We met by chance.

559
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,880
Yet you risked your life to save me.

560
00:27:11,359 --> 00:27:13,160
Brother, your righteousness reaches the clouds.

561
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:15,920
If in this life...

562
00:27:15,920 --> 00:27:17,759
I could have a big brother like you...

563
00:27:18,119 --> 00:27:19,720
It would be the fortune of three lifetimes.

564
00:27:20,799 --> 00:27:23,880
I've always loved making friends with heroes.

565
00:27:24,079 --> 00:27:25,839
You're upright, I'm straightforward.

566
00:27:26,079 --> 00:27:28,000
Let's become sworn brothers right now.

567
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,079
I, Wei San.

568
00:27:33,519 --> 00:27:35,599
I, Fan Pengju.

569
00:27:35,839 --> 00:27:38,599
Share blessings, share hardships.

570
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:40,880
Fatty.

571
00:27:42,759 --> 00:27:43,640
Let me tell you.

572
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:44,880
If you see anyone suspicious these couple of days...

573
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:45,880
Remember to report to me.

574
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:46,799
Yes, sir.

575
00:27:51,519 --> 00:27:52,480
Does this actually work?

576
00:27:53,039 --> 00:27:54,160
It varies from person to person.

577
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:56,160
It works for me, but maybe not for you.

578
00:27:59,279 --> 00:27:59,839
Sir.

579
00:28:00,519 --> 00:28:02,200
Please close the door for me.

580
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,960
Close my ass.

581
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:13,920
He's gone.

582
00:28:14,839 --> 00:28:15,839
We didn't finish bowing just now.

583
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:17,000
Let's continue bowing.

584
00:28:17,319 --> 00:28:18,000
No need, no need.

585
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,680
We can just kowtow directly.

586
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:20,440
Okay.

587
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:28,079
From now on...

588
00:28:28,279 --> 00:28:30,319
...we are sworn brothers.

589
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:32,599
Brother.

590
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,200
Big Brother.

591
00:28:39,519 --> 00:28:41,319
Let us part ways here.

592
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,000
All right.

593
00:28:45,599 --> 00:28:46,400
Farewell.

594
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:55,599
That won't work.

595
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:57,400
Looking like this...

596
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:59,039
...you'll get caught the moment you step out.

597
00:29:02,119 --> 00:29:03,400
Big Brother is truly Big Brother.

598
00:29:03,839 --> 00:29:05,400
You are cautious and wise.

599
00:29:10,319 --> 00:29:11,519
I need to think...

600
00:29:12,519 --> 00:29:13,960
...about how to...

601
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,759
...get you out of the city.

602
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:17,720
Exactly.

603
00:29:22,079 --> 00:29:23,319
Come, come, come.

604
00:29:24,039 --> 00:29:24,480
Come.

605
00:29:26,039 --> 00:29:28,079
Go grab a bite at the tofu pudding shop ahead.

606
00:29:28,599 --> 00:29:29,799
Order some steamed pork belly.

607
00:29:29,799 --> 00:29:31,400
Have all the steamed rice you want. Go on.

608
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:32,400
Sure, sure, sure.

609
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:33,799
There's hard work ahead.

610
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,200
What are you up to?

611
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:43,880
I was thinking...

612
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:46,160
...you're about to get married.

613
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:49,079
You should go out of town...

614
00:29:49,279 --> 00:29:52,359
...to visit your mother's grave and burn paper money.

615
00:29:53,039 --> 00:29:54,240
Take this bridal sedan chair.

616
00:29:54,319 --> 00:29:55,559
Let your mother see...

617
00:29:55,759 --> 00:29:57,480
...that you're living a very good life now.

618
00:29:57,599 --> 00:29:59,440
Put her mind at ease.

619
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:00,880
You sure are thoughtful.

620
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,640
Young Master Huo is thoughtful too.

621
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,920
I asked to borrow it, and he agreed right away.

622
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:05,920
I'm not getting in.

623
00:30:07,559 --> 00:30:08,240
Why not?

624
00:30:09,759 --> 00:30:12,119
Does this sedan bite your butt?

625
00:30:12,599 --> 00:30:14,519
Doing this is like selling me off.

626
00:30:15,319 --> 00:30:16,319
What do you mean?

627
00:30:16,599 --> 00:30:17,480
Can't you tell?

628
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:18,920
I don't want to marry him at all.

629
00:30:20,519 --> 00:30:23,839
Young Master Huo is educated and gentle.

630
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:26,000
Why wouldn't you want to marry him?

631
00:30:26,160 --> 00:30:28,240
I can't explain it in a sentence or two.

632
00:30:28,319 --> 00:30:29,119
Anyway, I'm not sitting in it.

633
00:30:32,079 --> 00:30:33,680
I've already borrowed it.

634
00:30:34,799 --> 00:30:35,920
Just sit in it for a bit.

635
00:30:36,359 --> 00:30:37,839
Consider it doing me a favor.

636
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:41,680
What scheme do you have up your sleeve?

637
00:30:43,480 --> 00:30:45,160
Just a trip out of the city.

638
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:47,000
As for the reason...

639
00:30:47,799 --> 00:30:48,799
...I can't tell you.

640
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,759
As long as you agree...

641
00:30:51,880 --> 00:30:53,640
...I'll repay you double in the future.

642
00:30:57,319 --> 00:30:58,559
It's not impossible.

643
00:30:59,599 --> 00:31:01,119
But if I help you this time...

644
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,039
...you have to help me next time.

645
00:31:03,359 --> 00:31:04,000
I definitely will.

646
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:06,680
A gentleman's word is his bond.

647
00:31:07,039 --> 00:31:08,599
Hurry up and get ready.

648
00:31:09,079 --> 00:31:10,319
We'll make it a quick trip.

649
00:31:27,079 --> 00:31:28,519
Let's go, let's go.

650
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:29,240
Go.

651
00:31:30,319 --> 00:31:30,839
Hurry up.

652
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:32,319
I told them...

653
00:31:32,319 --> 00:31:34,319
...that I tied up a pig to take to the grave.

654
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,000
What are you saying?

655
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,119
You want me to pretend to be a pig?

656
00:31:40,480 --> 00:31:41,799
Just bear with it.

657
00:31:41,799 --> 00:31:42,519
Fine, fine, fine.

658
00:31:46,319 --> 00:31:47,640
It's too small, I can't squeeze in.

659
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,519
Just squeeze harder.
